  "prompt": "I scored 570 in neet 2 . What would be my expected rank, in total from neet 1 & 2?",
  "response": "NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) is typically conducted as a single examination in India. There isn't a separate NEET 1 and NEET 2 for the same year. If you are referring to scores from different attempts or years, the ranking will depend on the specific year's examination and the performance of other candidates.\n\nHowever, if you scored 570 in NEET, your expected rank can vary based on the overall difficulty of the exam and the performance of other candidates. Historically, a score of 570 might have placed you roughly within the range of 15,000 to 25,000 ranks, but this is a rough estimate and can vary year to year.\n\nTo get a more accurate prediction, you may want to check the official NEET rank predictors available online, which take into account the data from the specific year of your examination.\n\nIf there is a misunderstanding or if you have specific details regarding \"NEET 1 & 2,\" please provide more context for a more precise answer.",
